            <h3 class="featurette-heading">Extreme Weather</h3>
            <p class="lead">Extreme weather can have a big impact in a short time.  Climate models predict significant changes in the frequency and intensity of some extreme weather events over the coming decades.  New Yorkers can expect more and longer-lasting heat waves and fewer extreme cold events as well as more heavy rainfalls and short-duration droughts.  These events affect energy systems, agriculture, air quality, water quality, infrastructure, and ecosystems.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

