            <h3 class="featurette-heading">Snowpack Decline</h3>
            <p class="lead">The accumulation of winter snow is projected to decline sharply by the end of this century.  This decline has implications for New York’s water supply and for tourism.  Skiing and snowmobiling contribute close to $2 billion to New York State’s economy each year, and the success of these recreational industries depends directly on a healthy snowpack.  </p>
          </div>
