            <h3 class="featurette-heading">Growing Regions</h3>
            <p class="lead">Agriculture is an important business sector in New York, contributing nearly $5 billion to the state’s economy. Climate change offers some opportunities for farmers, including longer growing seasons that can mean higher yields, the ability to grow varieties of wine grapes that previously grew only in Europe, and the chance to grow new crops.  Extreme heat events will stress dairy and apple farms, however, and farmers will face water management challenges brought on by more frequent heavy rainfall events and drought.</p>
